SIMPLE: reclination
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Reclination
<hw>Rec`li*na"tion</hw> <pr>(r⟦ecr⟧k`l⟦icr⟧*n⟦amac⟧"sh⟦ucr⟧n)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F. <ets>r⟦eacute⟧clinaison</ets>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of leaning or reclining, or the state of being
reclined.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Dialing)</fld> <def>The angle which the plane of
the dial makes with a vertical plane which it intersects in a horizontal
line.</def> <rj><au>Brande & C.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Surg.)</fld> <def>The act or process of removing a
cataract, by applying the needle to its anterior surface, and depressing
it into the vitreous humor in such a way that the front surface of the
cataract becomes the upper one and its back surface the lower one.</def>
<rj><au>Dunglison.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Recline</ent>⟦br⟧
